## Code Quality

This project uses several tools to maintain code quality and consistency.

### Pre-commit Hooks

Pre-commit hooks automatically check your code before each commit, catching common issues early.

**Install hooks** (if not already done):
```bash
pre-commit install
```

**Run manually** on all files:
```bash
pre-commit run --all-files
```

**What pre-commit checks**:
- **Ruff**: Linting and formatting
- **File validation**: Trailing whitespace, end-of-file newlines, YAML/JSON syntax
- **Codespell**: Common spelling mistakes

**Skipping hooks** (not recommended):
```bash
git commit --no-verify
```

Once installed, pre-commit runs automatically on `git commit` and will prevent commits with issues. Fix the reported problems and commit again.

### Ruff (Linting and Formatting)

This project uses [Ruff](https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/) for fast linting and formatting.

**Check for issues**:
```bash
ruff check .
```

**Auto-fix issues**:
```bash
ruff check --fix .
```

**Format code**:
```bash
ruff format .
```

**Check before committing** (done automatically by pre-commit):
```bash
ruff check . && ruff format --check .
```

### Type Checking (Optional)

For stricter type checking, you can add mypy:

```bash
uv pip install mypy
mypy custom_components/{{ component_slug }}
```

